title: Frogtown Creek
text:
Frogtown Creek is a stream in <a href="Lumpkin%20County%2C%20Georgia">Lumpkin County, Georgia</a>, in the <a href="United%20States">United States</a>.
Frogtown is the figurative English translation of the <a href="Cherokee%20language">Cherokee language</a> name, which literally means "frog place". An Indian village once stood near the creek's bank.
